es in the U.S. plunging, a good portion of the Treasury yield curve inverting, consumer spending decelerating for three straight quarters and no end to the trade war with China in sight, it may well be advisable for the Fed to “take back” its December rate cut as early as Wednesday.
A key manufacturing gauge just saw its biggest one-month decline in 18 years
