ew weeks for U.S. trade relations with China and Mexico.” J.P. Morgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon said lawmakers need to “work together to enact policies that will encourage inclusive growth, innovation and opportunity in the United States. That includes investing in infrastructure and workforce training, reforming our immigration system and expanding free and fair trade.” Subscribe to CNBC on YouTube.
‘Tariff Man’ Trump heads to Iowa, a state scarred by his trade war ahead of 2020
