r dual mandate has served us extremely well,” Evans said. “I think we have to be careful about where the economy is and where we think it’s going.” The tendency of inflation to run persistently below the Fed’s 2% goal has him “a little nervous.” Evans added that he would be “more aggressive” in defending the Fed’s symmetric target, meaning that policymakers would be comfortable with inflation running slightly above or below the goal. “I think we should be overshooting 2%,” he said.
